Fjer Host Analysis Tool

Dependencies:
Python 2.7
pywin32: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pywin32
python WMI: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/WMI/
netaddr: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/netaddr

Run HRT.py with desired switches.

If run run without -r or --remote, the program will run the provided switches on the local system. If run with 
-r or --remote, ensure you run the command line with an account that has permission to run WMI on the remote 
system. The system data WMI command is run automatically if a database is selected.

The script must be run with administrator priviledges. For remote targets, it must be run with an account with 
administrator priviledges on the remote target, and the remote target must have WMI queries and SMB allowed.

  -h, --help            show help message and exit
  -d DB, --db DB        Provide database name or full path to specify location
  -o, --stout           Send results to Standard Out
  --verbose             Print verbose results
  -i IP, --ipaddr IP	IP Address or CIDR-Notation range of IP Addresses. Exclude for Local Machine
  --username            User Name for remote system (must be used with -r)
  --password            Password for remote system (must be used with -r and -u)
  -A, --all             Run all switches
  -y, --sysinfo         Gather System Information
  -u, --users           User account data
  -n, --netlogin        Network Login data
  -g, --groups          Group data
  -l, --ldisks          Logical Disk data
  -t, --timezone        Timezone data
  -s, --startup         Startup Program data
  --profiles            User Profiles data
  -a, --adapters        Netork Adapter data
  -P, --process         Processes data
  -S, --services        Services data
  -r, --shares          Shared Resources data
  -D, --pdisks          Physical Disk data
  -m, --memory          Physical Memory data
  -p, --ports           Open Ports
  --patches             Currently Applied Patches
  --arp                 Arp Table Data
  --routes              Routing Table Data
  -w, --wireless        Wireless Connection Data
  -b, --bios            BIOS Data
  --pnp                 Plug-n-play Devices Data
  --drivers             Drivers Data
